        <headline>Extreme Heat Warning issued August 8 at 12:18AM MST until August 8 at 8:00PM MST by NWS Flagstaff AZ</headline>
        <description>* WHAT...Dangerously hot conditions, daytime temperatures up to 112
degrees below 4000 feet.

* WHERE...Northern Gila County and Yavapai County Valleys and Basins.

* WHEN...Until 8 PM MST this evening.

* IMPACTS...Most individuals will be at risk for heat-related
illnesses without effective cooling or adequate hydration,
especially with prolonged outdoor exposure.
</description>
        <instruction>Drink plenty of fluids, stay in an air-conditioned room, stay out of
the sun, and check up on relatives and neighbors.

Do not leave young children and pets in unattended vehicles. Car
interiors will reach lethal temperatures in a matter of minutes.

Take action when you see symptoms of heat exhaustion and heat
stroke. Anyone overcome by heat should be moved to a cool and shaded
location. Heat stroke is an emergency! Call 9 1 1.

Stay cool, stay hydrated, stay informed.</instruction>
